snippet: Aaron Rose’s early 1960s photographs of Coney Island beachgoers will be on display at the Museum of the City of New York.
abstract: Photographer Aaron Rose documented fleshy display of Coney Island's beaches for three years beginning in 1961; 70 of his prints will be displayed for first time at Museum of City of New York beginning in May.
lead_paragraph: Aaron Rose’s early 1960s photographs of Coney Island beachgoers will be on display at the Museum of the City of New York.
